******
[2] Nebraska
Date: Tue 18 Apr 2017
Source: The North Platte Telegraph [edited]
http://www.nptelegraph.com/news/local_news/additional-cases-of-measles-suspected-in-the-area/article_5eb5e840-2474-11e7-bbfd-8301753d0cd3.html


As health officials investigate 3 more suspected measles cases in the region, the North Platte Public Schools announced that non-immunized students will be barred from classes and school activities for the next week [week of 23 April 2017].

"Students that have a weakened immune system and those who not fully immunized are at the highest risk of contracting measles," said Stuart Simpson, executive director of finance, facilities and operations, in a recorded call that went out to parents on [Tue 18 Apr 2017].

"Due to state regulations, the North Platte Public School District will be excluding non-immunized students from school and school related activities through [Thu 27 Apr 2017]."

The West Central District Health Department confirmed one case of measles over the weekend and said that 3 patients are going through additional tests after coming down with "measles-like symptoms."

According to the statement issued by the department on [Tue 18 Apr 2017], individuals who visited the locations [listed in the report at the URL above] during the specified time frames may have been exposed to the virus.

[Byline: Kamie Stephen]

