Australia
[6] New South Wales, Sydney
Date: Fri 21 Apr 2017 7:55PM
Source: The Sydney Morning Herald [edited]
http://www.smh.com.au/national/health/nsw-measles-count-climbs-to-23-latest-infectious-case-spent-time-at-powerhouse-museum-liverpool-westfield-20170421-gvpq14.html


Sydney's measles patient count continues to rise, with the latest infectious person spending time at [locations listed in the URL above.]

NSW Health is urging people between 20 and 40-years-old to check they have been fully immunized against the infectious disease, reporting the latest person to contract measles only had their 1st dose of the vaccine.

For further information visit: https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/
The most recent case brings to 17 the number of patients connected to an outbreak in western Sydney, and the total number of NSW measles cases so far this year [2017] to 23.

"Our public health units are contacting people known to have been in those locations to offer preventive injections, as appropriate. However, it will not be possible to identify and contact all people who may have been exposed to the disease," Director of Communicable Disease at NSW Health Vicky Sheppeard said.

[Byline: Kate Aubusson]

